snippet.title: 23 SMART LIFE HACKS FOR EVERY OCCASION
snippet.description:
Ways to make your life easier with these fantastic hacks. 

As we go through life, we come across little problems that seem unsolvable. But today, we‚Äôre going to show you some fun tricks you can try that will help save you time and hassle. Like when you have to sign a bunch of documents all at once. One way to fix that is to tape some pens on a piece of paper (Somewhat diagonally) and then use them to write. Now let‚Äôs head to the kitchen, where you need to make perfectly round crepes for your guests. You don‚Äôt need to buy an expensive crepe tool that flattens them out and turns them into a perfect circle ‚Äî you just need a chopstick or a skewer instead. You break it in the middle, create a 90-degree angle, and voila. Did you know you can use an old highlighter to paint or write stuff down on your tablet? Watch the video to see how to do it.

snippet.description:
#RepublicDay Parade 2021 ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§∏‡•Ä‡§ß‡§æ ‡§™‡•ç‡§∞‡§∏‡§æ‡§∞‡§£ | 26 January Parade Live
#RepublicDayparade #RepublicDay2021 #IndiaRepublicDay #‡§ó‡§£‡§§‡§Ç‡§§‡•ç‡§∞‡§¶‡§ø‡§µ‡§∏ 
India celebrates her 72nd Republic Day on 26 January 2021. We at Doordarshan extend our warm regards to all Indians in the country as well as abroad. It is the proud privilege of Doordarshan, India's National Broadcaster to LIVE-STREAM the magnificent 72nd Republic Day Parade - after our historic initiative in 2013 - on our official channel on YouTube. www.youtube/DoordarshanNational. Doordarshan has been telecasting the Republic Day Parade LIVE since the early sixties when cameras and equipment had to be taken out of the existing studio for this event! Today, for the ninth consecutive year, we will LIVE-STREAM the Republic Day Parade. Proud Indians and Indophiles from all over the world will be watching, along with our viewers from the freezing climate of Leh to the remotest corners of Kanyakumari, Thank you for always being with us - Friends of Doordarshan. We at Doordarshan extend our warm regards to all Indians in the country as well as abroad. It is the proud privilege of Doordarshan.

snippet.description:
In theaters and streaming exclusively on @HBOMax* March 26.

---

From Warner Bros. Pictures and Legendary Pictures comes the long-awaited face-off between two icons, ‚ÄúGodzilla vs. Kong,‚Äù the next epic adventure in Legendary‚Äôs cinematic Monsterverse, directed by Adam Wingard.

Legends collide in ‚ÄúGodzilla vs. Kong‚Äù as these mythic adversaries meet in a spectacular battle for the ages, with the fate of the world hanging in the balance.  Kong and his protectors undertake a perilous journey to find his true home, and with them is Jia, a young orphaned girl with whom he has formed a unique and powerful bond.  But they unexpectedly find themselves in the path of an enraged Godzilla, cutting a swath of destruction across the globe.  The epic clash between the two titans‚Äîinstigated by unseen forces‚Äîis only the beginning of the mystery that lies deep within the core of the Earth.

The film stars Alexander Skarsg√•rd (‚ÄúBig Little Lies,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Little Drummer Girl‚Äù), Millie Bobby Brown (‚ÄúStranger Things‚Äù), Rebecca Hall (‚ÄúChristine,‚Äù ‚ÄúProfessor Marston and the Wonder Women‚Äù), Brian Tyree Henry (‚ÄúJoker,‚Äù ‚ÄúSpider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse‚Äù), Shun Oguri (‚ÄúWeathering with You‚Äù), Eiza Gonz√°lez (‚ÄúFast & Furious Presents: Hobbs & Shaw‚Äù), Julian Dennison (‚ÄúDeadpool 2‚Äù), with Kyle Chandler (‚ÄúGodzilla: King of the Monsters‚Äù) and Demi√°n Bichir (‚ÄúThe Nun,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Hateful Eight‚Äù).
Wingard (‚ÄúThe Guest,‚Äù ‚ÄúYou‚Äôre Next‚Äù) directed from a screenplay by Eric Pearson (‚ÄúThor: Ragnarok‚Äù) and Max Borenstein (‚ÄúGodzilla: King of the Monsters,‚Äù ‚ÄúKong: Skull Island‚Äù), story by Terry Rossio (‚ÄúPirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales‚Äù) and Michael Dougherty & Zach Shields (‚ÄúGodzilla: King of the Monsters‚Äù), based on the character ‚ÄúGodzilla‚Äù owned and created by TOHO CO., LTD.  The film was produced by Mary Parent, Alex Garcia, Eric McLeod, Jon Jashni, Thomas Tull and Brian Rogers, with Jay Ashenfelter, Herbert W. Gains, Dan Lin, Roy Lee, Yoshimitsu Banno and Kenji Okuhira executive producing.

The director‚Äôs behind-the-scenes creative team included director of photography Ben Seresin (‚ÄúThe Mummy,‚Äù ‚ÄúWorld War Z‚Äù), production designers Owen Paterson (‚ÄúJumanji: Welcome to the Jungle,‚Äù ‚ÄúGodzilla‚Äù) and Thomas S. Hammock (‚ÄúBlair Witch‚Äù), editor Josh Schaeffer (‚ÄúGodzilla: King of the Monsters‚Äù), costume designer Ann Foley (‚ÄúSkyscraper‚Äù) and visual effects supervisor John ‚ÄúDJ‚Äù DesJardin (upcoming ‚ÄúZack Snyder‚Äôs Justice League‚Äù).

Warner Bros. Pictures and Legendary Pictures Present a Legendary Pictures Production, A Film By Adam Wingard, ‚ÄúGodzilla vs. Kong.‚Äù  The film will be released nationwide in 2D and 3D in select theaters and IMAX on March 26, 2021 and will be available in the U.S. on HBO Max for 31 days from theatrical release.  It is rated PG-13 for intense sequences of creature violence/destruction and brief language.

On March 5, join Raya on her quest to find the last dragon. See Disney‚Äôs Raya and the Last Dragon in theaters or order it on Disney+ with Premier Access on March 5. Learn more: http://disney.com/raya  

About Raya and the Last Dragon: 
 
‚ÄúRaya and the Last Dragon‚Äù takes us on an exciting, epic journey to the fantasy world of Kumandra, where humans and dragons lived together long ago in harmony. But when an evil force threatened the land, the dragons sacrificed themselves to save humanity. Now, 500 years later, that same evil has returned and it‚Äôs up to a lone warrior, Raya, to track down the legendary last dragon to restore the fractured land and its divided people. However, along her journey, she‚Äôll learn that it‚Äôll take more than a dragon to save the world‚Äîit‚Äôs going to take trust and teamwork as well.

‚ÄúRaya and the Last Dragon‚Äù features an outstanding voice cast, including Kelly Marie Tran as the voice of the intrepid warrior Raya; Awkwafina as the legendary dragon, Sisu; Gemma Chan as Raya‚Äôs nemesis, Namaari; Daniel Dae Kim as Raya‚Äôs visionary father, Benja; Sandra Oh as Namaari‚Äôs powerful mother, Virana; Benedict Wong as Tong, a formidable giant; Izaac Wang as Boun, a 10-year-old entrepreneur; Thalia Tran as the mischievous toddler Little Noi; Alan Tudyk as Tuk Tuk, Raya‚Äôs best friend and trusty steed; Lucille Soong as Dang Hu, the leader of the land of Talon; Patti Harrison as the chief of the Tail land; and Ross Butler as chief of the Spine land.

LAKERS at 76ERS | FULL GAME HIGHLIGHTS | January 27, 2021

Tobias Harris knocked down a go-ahead basket with 2.4 seconds remaining in regulation to lift the Philadelphia 76ers over the Los Angeles Lakers, 107-106, handing the Lakers their first road loss of the season. Joel Embiid (28 PTS, 6 REB, 4 AST) and Tobias Harris (24 PTS, 7 REB) led the way for the 76ers, while Ben Simmons added 17 PTS, 11 REB and 10 AST in the victory, the 31st triple-double of his career. LeBron James tallied 34 PTS, 6 REB and 6 AST for the Lakers.

snippet.title: Perseverance Mars Rover Pre-Landing News Conference
snippet.description:
After nearly 300 million miles, our Perseverance rover completes its journey to Mars on Feb. 18, 2021. To reach the surface of the Red Planet, it has to survive the harrowing final phase known as Entry, Descent, and Landing.

On Jan. 27 at 4:30 p.m. EST, find out more about the upcoming landing from the scientists and engineers on the team:¬†

Thomas Zurbuchen, associate administrator, Science Mission Directorate, NASA Headquarters
Lori Glaze, director, Planetary Science Division, NASA Headquarters
Matt Wallace, Mars 2020 deputy project manager, JPL
Allen Chen, Mars 2020 entry, descent, and landing lead, JPL
Ken Farley, Mars 2020 project scientist, Caltech
Briony Horgan, Mars 2020 science team member, Purdue University

snippet.title: How to Repair a DEEP SCRATCH in Car Paint (DIY)
snippet.description:
Learn how to repair a deep scratch in the paint of your car. In this case someone keyed my car so I will show you how to remove a deep scratch from that using a touch up paint pen. Fixing scratches in your car's paint is simple and if they are just clear coat scratches it is even easier. 

To remove deep scratches you need to clean the scratch, sand the scratch, use touchup paint on the scratch, sand that paint smooth with the factory paint job, add clear coat, and wet sand that smooth with the factory paint. Then you can polish the whole panel and you are done!

Clear Coat Scratch Repair: https://youtu.be/2nYF46P7B2c

Paint Pen: https://advanceautoparts.rt8x.net/voOO3
1000-1500-2000 Grit:  https://advanceautoparts.rt8x.net/mD0b7
3000 Grit Sandpaper: https://advanceautoparts.rt8x.net/x0Rbx
5000 Grit Sandpaper: https://advanceautoparts.rt8x.net/QRWea
Polish: https://advanceautoparts.rt8x.net/rABbj
Polishing Pad: https://amzn.to/2YcLJEG
Microfiber Towel: http://amzn.to/1TQK01h
Tape: http://amzn.to/1SEBgtL

snippet.title: Danny MacAskill - The Slabs
snippet.description:
Subscribe for more: https://www.youtube.com/dannymacaskill?sub_confirmation=1

A Danny MacAskill film by Peny - https://www.wearepeny.com/  

With many of our overseas filming plans cancelled as a result of recent times myself and the crew decided to look a little closer to home for our latest film. 

I am a big fan of rock climbing and have been inspired by the various men and woman who set new routes and test themselves on some amazing faces around the world so I set out to find some challenging Slab Rock routes on my home Island of Skye with an aim to ride them in a continuous line and test what was possible on my bike. The remote Dubh Slabs rising out of Loch Coruisk in the heart of the Black Cuilin ridge provided some of the steepest terrain I have ever ridden as well as an amazing back drop for the film. 

The remote location and steep face forced us to think outside the box and meant we had to move away from traditional filming techniques, with us opting to shoot the entire film using GoPros mounted on myself and an FPV (First Person View) racing drone.

Music: 
Arcade Fire - No Cars Go: https://youtu.be/WaIRsqjzsKo

snippet.localized.title: Danny MacAskill - The Slabs
snippet.localized.description:
Subscribe for more: https://www.youtube.com/dannymacaskill?sub_confirmation=1

A Danny MacAskill film by Peny - https://www.wearepeny.com/  

With many of our overseas filming plans cancelled as a result of recent times myself and the crew decided to look a little closer to home for our latest film. 

I am a big fan of rock climbing and have been inspired by the various men and woman who set new routes and test themselves on some amazing faces around the world so I set out to find some challenging Slab Rock routes on my home Island of Skye with an aim to ride them in a continuous line and test what was possible on my bike. The remote Dubh Slabs rising out of Loch Coruisk in the heart of the Black Cuilin ridge provided some of the steepest terrain I have ever ridden as well as an amazing back drop for the film. 

The remote location and steep face forced us to think outside the box and meant we had to move away from traditional filming techniques, with us opting to shoot the entire film using GoPros mounted on myself and an FPV (First Person View) racing drone.

snippet.title: Welcome to The Arsenal, Martin Odegaard | First Interview
snippet.description:
Norwegian international Martin Odegaard is joining us from Real Madrid on loan for the remainder of the season.

Technical director Edu said: ‚ÄúWe are delighted to welcome Martin to the club until the end of the season. I would like to thank everyone at Real Madrid and Martin‚Äôs representatives for their collaboration in making this loan move happen. Martin is an exceptional talent and we are strengthening our squad by introducing an exciting offensive player to the club for the remaining months of this season.‚Äù 

Mikel Arteta said: ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs great that we‚Äôve secured Martin to come to us until the end of the season. Martin is of course a player that we all know very well and although still young, he has been playing at the top level for a while. Martin will provide us with quality offensive options and we‚Äôre all excited to be integrating him into our plans between now and May.‚Äù

'It seems like a great project and a great club!'

The attacking midfielder started his career in Norway with Stromsgodset, where he made his debut as a 15-year-old in April 2014, becoming the youngest-ever player to feature in the top division. After featuring regularly in the Stromsgodset team in his first season, Odegaard was signed by Real Madrid in January 2015 and subsequently became their youngest player in May 2015. 

In the three seasons from 2017/18, Martin spent loan spells with Heerenveen and Vitesse Arnhem in the Netherlands and then last season back in Spain with Real Sociedad, where he helped the club reach the final of the Copa Del Rey and also qualify for the Europa League.

The 22-year-old has also made 25 appearances for Norway, making his debut in August 2014 when he became the youngest debutant for his country‚Äôs senior national team at the age of just 15 years and 253 days. 

Martin will wear the number 11 shirt.

Everyone at Arsenal welcomes Martin to the club.

The loan agreement is subject to the completion of legal and regulatory processes.

snippet.title: These Ponds Help Support Half The People On Earth
snippet.description:
What are these electric blue ponds in the middle of the Utah desert? And why do they keep changing color?

Join Derek Muller (Veritasium) as he looks into the weird, bizarre, and seemingly inexplicable images found on Google Earth to discover what on Earth they actually are. It‚Äôs a travel vlog, documentary, and science show wrapped into one. It‚Äôs Pindrop.

snippet.title: 16-year-old detained under Singapore's Internal Security Act after planning to attack two mosques
snippet.description:
A 16-year-old has been detained under Singapore's Internal Security Act. He had planned to attack Muslims at two local mosques on the second anniversary of the Christchurch attacks on March 15. The authorities said the secondary school student is the youngest to be detained under the act, and the first to be inspired by far-right extremist ideology. The youth is a Protestant Christian of Indian ethnicity. He had planned to attack Muslims at Assyafaah Mosque and Yusof Ishak Mosque. The mosques are about 4km apart and located near his home.

snippet.title: Godzilla vs. Kong ‚Äì Official Trailer
snippet.description:
In theaters and streaming exclusively on @HBOMax* March 26.
¬†
*Available on @HBOMax in the US only, for 31 days, at no extra cost to subscribers.

https://www.godzillavskong.com/
https://www.facebook.com/GodzillaVsKong

---

From Warner Bros. Pictures and Legendary Pictures comes the long-awaited face-off between two icons, ‚ÄúGodzilla vs. Kong,‚Äù the next epic adventure in Legendary‚Äôs cinematic Monsterverse, directed by Adam Wingard.

Legends collide in ‚ÄúGodzilla vs. Kong‚Äù as these mythic adversaries meet in a spectacular battle for the ages, with the fate of the world hanging in the balance.  Kong and his protectors undertake a perilous journey to find his true home, and with them is Jia, a young orphaned girl with whom he has formed a unique and powerful bond.  But they unexpectedly find themselves in the path of an enraged Godzilla, cutting a swath of destruction across the globe.  The epic clash between the two titans‚Äîinstigated by unseen forces‚Äîis only the beginning of the mystery that lies deep within the core of the Earth.

The film stars Alexander Skarsg√•rd (‚ÄúBig Little Lies,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Little Drummer Girl‚Äù), Millie Bobby Brown (‚ÄúStranger Things‚Äù), Rebecca Hall (‚ÄúChristine,‚Äù ‚ÄúProfessor Marston and the Wonder Women‚Äù), Brian Tyree Henry (‚ÄúJoker,‚Äù ‚ÄúSpider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse‚Äù), Shun Oguri (‚ÄúWeathering with You‚Äù), Eiza Gonz√°lez (‚ÄúFast & Furious Presents: Hobbs & Shaw‚Äù), Julian Dennison (‚ÄúDeadpool 2‚Äù), with Kyle Chandler (‚ÄúGodzilla: King of the Monsters‚Äù) and Demi√°n Bichir (‚ÄúThe Nun,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Hateful Eight‚Äù).
Wingard (‚ÄúThe Guest,‚Äù ‚ÄúYou‚Äôre Next‚Äù) directed from a screenplay by Eric Pearson (‚ÄúThor: Ragnarok‚Äù) and Max Borenstein (‚ÄúGodzilla: King of the Monsters,‚Äù ‚ÄúKong: Skull Island‚Äù), story by Terry Rossio (‚ÄúPirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales‚Äù) and Michael Dougherty & Zach Shields (‚ÄúGodzilla: King of the Monsters‚Äù), based on the character ‚ÄúGodzilla‚Äù owned and created by TOHO CO., LTD.  The film was produced by Mary Parent, Alex Garcia, Eric McLeod, Jon Jashni, Thomas Tull and Brian Rogers, with Jay Ashenfelter, Herbert W. Gains, Dan Lin, Roy Lee, Yoshimitsu Banno and Kenji Okuhira executive producing.

The director‚Äôs behind-the-scenes creative team included director of photography Ben Seresin (‚ÄúThe Mummy,‚Äù ‚ÄúWorld War Z‚Äù), production designers Owen Paterson (‚ÄúJumanji: Welcome to the Jungle,‚Äù ‚ÄúGodzilla‚Äù) and Thomas S. Hammock (‚ÄúBlair Witch‚Äù), editor Josh Schaeffer (‚ÄúGodzilla: King of the Monsters‚Äù), costume designer Ann Foley (‚ÄúSkyscraper‚Äù) and visual effects supervisor John ‚ÄúDJ‚Äù DesJardin (upcoming ‚ÄúZack Snyder‚Äôs Justice League‚Äù).

Warner Bros. Pictures and Legendary Pictures Present a Legendary Pictures Production, A Film By Adam Wingard, ‚ÄúGodzilla vs. Kong.‚Äù  The film will be released nationwide in 2D and 3D in select theaters and IMAX on March 26, 2021 and will be available in the U.S. on HBO Max for 31 days from theatrical release.  It is rated PG-13 for intense sequences of creature violence/destruction and brief language.

Each week night, THE LATE LATE SHOW with JAMES CORDEN throws the ultimate late night after party with a mix of celebrity guests, edgy musical acts, games and sketches. Corden differentiates his show by offering viewers a peek behind-the-scenes into the green room, bringing all of his guests out at once and lending his musical and acting talents to various sketches. Additionally, bandleader Reggie Watts and the house band provide original, improvised music throughout the show. Since Corden took the reigns as host in March 2015, he has quickly become known for generating buzzworthy viral videos, such as Carpool Karaoke."

snippet.title: WATCH LIVE: The presidential inauguration of Joe Biden and Kamala Harris ‚Äî 1/20/21
snippet.description:
Joe Biden is set to become the nation‚Äôs 46th president today. He is slated to take the oath of office around noon, which is when Donald Trump‚Äôs term as president ends. Sign up for CNBC Pro to stream the inauguration with commentary: http://cnb.cx/3iC88Vl

Set against a backdrop of a locked-down Washington, D.C., and a socially distanced ceremony, Biden, in his inaugural address, is expected to plead for national unity as political, economic and health care crises grip the nation. He will take over the presidency two weeks after a deadly pro-Trump riot at Capitol Hill and as deaths from Covid-19 continue to surge. Since the pandemic began early last year, the disease has killed more than 400,000 people in the United States.

Kamala Harris will make history as the country‚Äôs first Black, female and South Asian vice president.

The first members of Biden‚Äôs Cabinet are slated to be sworn in over the next few days, as well, including Janet Yellen as Treasury secretary. Biden‚Äôs Democratic Party, likewise, will assume a bare majority in the Senate after three new lawmakers ‚Äì Raphael Warnock and Jon Ossoff of Georgia, and Alex Padilla of California ‚Äì also take their oaths of office.

snippet.title: Is Godzilla The Bad Guy In Godzilla vs. Kong?
snippet.description:
We've finally got our first real look at Godzilla vs. Kong and while there's certainly a lot to unpack in this trailer, perhaps the biggest question is: what's the deal with Godzilla and why is he being such a jerk?

The epic next chapter in the cinematic Monsterverse pits two of the greatest icons in motion picture history against one another - the fearsome Godzilla and the mighty Kong - with humanity caught in the balance. 

Godzilla Vs. Kong comes to cinemas and HBO Max in 2021 and stars Alexander Skarsg√•rd, Millie Bobby Brown and Rebecca Hall. Godzilla Vs. Kong is directed by Adam Wingard (Blair Witch, Death Note) and is the latest film is Warner Bros Monsterverse, following on from Gareth Edwards' Godzilla, Kong: Skull Island  and Godzilla: King of the Monsters.  
   
In a time when monsters walk the Earth, humanity‚Äôs fight for its future sets Godzilla and Kong on a collision course that will see the two most powerful forces of nature on the planet collide in a spectacular battle for the ages. As Monarch embarks on a perilous mission into uncharted terrain and unearths clues to the Titans‚Äô origins, a human conspiracy threatens to wipe the creatures, both good and bad, from the face of the earth forever.

snippet.title: WATCH: Harris escorts the Pences as they depart U.S. Capitol
snippet.description:
Skip to 12:49 to watch Harris and Emhoff escort the Pences down the Capitol steps.

Vice President Kamala Harris and second gentleman Douglas Emhoff escorted former Vice President Mike Pence and second lady Karen Pence to their departure from the U.S. Capitol after Harris and President Joe Biden were sworn in on Wednesday.

While former President Donald Trump never formally conceded to Biden, Pence called Harris to offer his congratulations and assistance in the transition five days ago.

snippet.title: Godzilla vs. Kong ‚Äì Official Trailer
snippet.description:
In theaters and streaming exclusively on @HBOMax* March 26.
¬†
*Available on @HBOMax in the US only, for 31 days, at no extra cost to subscribers.

https://www.godzillavskong.com/
https://www.facebook.com/GodzillaVsKong
https://www.instagram.com/godzillavskong/
https://twitter.com/GodzillaVsKong

---

From Warner Bros. Pictures and Legendary Pictures comes the long-awaited face-off between two icons, ‚ÄúGodzilla vs. Kong,‚Äù the next epic adventure in Legendary‚Äôs cinematic Monsterverse, directed by Adam Wingard.

Legends collide in ‚ÄúGodzilla vs. Kong‚Äù as these mythic adversaries meet in a spectacular battle for the ages, with the fate of the world hanging in the balance.  Kong and his protectors undertake a perilous journey to find his true home, and with them is Jia, a young orphaned girl with whom he has formed a unique and powerful bond.  But they unexpectedly find themselves in the path of an enraged Godzilla, cutting a swath of destruction across the globe.  The epic clash between the two titans‚Äîinstigated by unseen forces‚Äîis only the beginning of the mystery that lies deep within the core of the Earth.

The film stars Alexander Skarsg√•rd (‚ÄúBig Little Lies,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Little Drummer Girl‚Äù), Millie Bobby Brown (‚ÄúStranger Things‚Äù), Rebecca Hall (‚ÄúChristine,‚Äù ‚ÄúProfessor Marston and the Wonder Women‚Äù), Brian Tyree Henry (‚ÄúJoker,‚Äù ‚ÄúSpider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse‚Äù), Shun Oguri (‚ÄúWeathering with You‚Äù), Eiza Gonz√°lez (‚ÄúFast & Furious Presents: Hobbs & Shaw‚Äù), Julian Dennison (‚ÄúDeadpool 2‚Äù), with Kyle Chandler (‚ÄúGodzilla: King of the Monsters‚Äù) and Demi√°n Bichir (‚ÄúThe Nun,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Hateful Eight‚Äù).
Wingard (‚ÄúThe Guest,‚Äù ‚ÄúYou‚Äôre Next‚Äù) directed from a screenplay by Eric Pearson (‚ÄúThor: Ragnarok‚Äù) and Max Borenstein (‚ÄúGodzilla: King of the Monsters,‚Äù ‚ÄúKong: Skull Island‚Äù), story by Terry Rossio (‚ÄúPirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales‚Äù) and Michael Dougherty & Zach Shields (‚ÄúGodzilla: King of the Monsters‚Äù), based on the character ‚ÄúGodzilla‚Äù owned and created by TOHO CO., LTD.  The film was produced by Mary Parent, Alex Garcia, Eric McLeod, Jon Jashni, Thomas Tull and Brian Rogers, with Jay Ashenfelter, Herbert W. Gains, Dan Lin, Roy Lee, Yoshimitsu Banno and Kenji Okuhira executive producing.

The director‚Äôs behind-the-scenes creative team included director of photography Ben Seresin (‚ÄúThe Mummy,‚Äù ‚ÄúWorld War Z‚Äù), production designers Owen Paterson (‚ÄúJumanji: Welcome to the Jungle,‚Äù ‚ÄúGodzilla‚Äù) and Thomas S. Hammock (‚ÄúBlair Witch‚Äù), editor Josh Schaeffer (‚ÄúGodzilla: King of the Monsters‚Äù), costume designer Ann Foley (‚ÄúSkyscraper‚Äù) and visual effects supervisor John ‚ÄúDJ‚Äù DesJardin (upcoming ‚ÄúZack Snyder‚Äôs Justice League‚Äù).

Warner Bros. Pictures and Legendary Pictures Present a Legendary Pictures Production, A Film By Adam Wingard, ‚ÄúGodzilla vs. Kong.‚Äù  The film will be released nationwide in 2D and 3D in select theaters and IMAX on March 26, 2021 and will be available in the U.S. on HBO Max for 31 days from theatrical release.  It is rated PG-13 for intense sequences of creature violence/destruction and brief language.

snippet.title: Documenting America's Underbelly - ALL GAS NO BRAKES
snippet.description:
Andrew Callaghan's series ALL GAS NO BRAKES captures the underbelly of American culture as he crisscrosses the country in a rusty RV.¬† Interviewing¬†people on the fringes of society, the success of the show has made Andrew's oversized suit and bushy hair famous. In this episode of My Life Online, we meet up with Andrew and his crew in Sturgis, South Dakota for the annual motorcycle rally that is taking place during the COVID-19 pandemic to see how the sausage gets made.

snippet.title: HIGHLIGHTS | Southampton vs Arsenal (1-3) | Pepe, Saka & Lacazette fire us to victory
snippet.description:
We came from behind to claim all three points on the road and make it six games without defeat in the Premier League.

The forward line was in excellent form all evening with Nicolas Pepe, Bukayo Saka and Alexandre Lacazette all on target as we gained swift revenge for the weekend's FA Cup defeat here at St Mary's.

The Saints needed just three minutes to open the scoring, but we should have been ahead even before that. Granit Xhaka released Lacazette into the box, but the Frenchman's low shot was saved by the legs of Alex McCarthy as he bore down on goal.

The miss was compounded when the hosts went ahead through a thumping Stuart Armstrong volley from James Ward-Prowse's out-swinging corner.

We maintained our intensity though and got on terms through Pepe, who kept his cool inside the box to slide the ball into the corner after being set up by Xhaka.

Chances kept coming and it was certainly a more entertaining match than the FA Cup game here just three days ago, with Pepe and Saka seeing plenty of the ball on the wings.

The game eventually settled down, though it remained entertaining with both sides pushing men forward.

We went into the break in the lead thanks to a wonderful goal from Saka. Lacazette fed the youngster with a perfectly weighted pass, and the England man did the rest ‚Äì skipping past McCarthy and then calmly rolled the ball home right footed from outside the box. It was his fourth goal in his last six league starts - he is certainly enjoying life on the right wing.

It was a much more measured start to the second half. The game was on a knife edge as the hosts began to peg us back.

But our third goal killed their impetus. The impressive Cedric found Saka on the opposite flank, and his low cross was converted from close range by Lacazette.

Bernd Leno made a superb save from a Ward-Prowse free-kick late on and Rob Holding tackled Che Adams in the area as Southampton made us work until the last minute for the three points that lift us to eighth.

snippet.title: Danny MacAskill - The Slabs
snippet.description:
Subscribe for more: https://www.youtube.com/dannymacaskill?sub_confirmation=1

A Danny MacAskill film by Peny - https://www.wearepeny.com/  

With many of our overseas filming plans cancelled as a result of recent times myself and the crew decided to look a little closer to home for our latest film. 

I am a big fan of rock climbing and have been inspired by the various men and woman who set new routes and test themselves on some amazing faces around the world so I set out to find some challenging Slab Rock routes on my home Island of Skye with an aim to ride them in a continuous line and test what was possible on my bike. The remote Dubh Slabs rising out of Loch Coruisk in the heart of the Black Cuilin ridge provided some of the steepest terrain I have ever ridden as well as an amazing back drop for the film. 

The remote location and steep face forced us to think outside the box and meant we had to move away from traditional filming techniques, with us opting to shoot the entire film using GoPros mounted on myself and an FPV (First Person View) racing drone.

snippet.title: 5 Fakten, die ihr √ºber Auschwitz wissen solltet | Terra X
snippet.description:
Das Vernichtungslager Auschwitz ‚Äì Endstation f√ºr √ºber eine Million Menschen. Wir haben Euch in diesem Video 5 Fakten zusammengefasst, die ihr √ºber Auschwitz wissen solltet: Auschwitz hat Vorl√§ufer. Seit Beginn des Dritten Reiches entstehen √ºberall in Deutschland so genannte Konzentrationslager, kurz KZ, in denen politische Gegner inhaftiert werden. Im Mai 1940 wird in Auschwitz ein weiteres KZ gegr√ºndet. Der Ort liegt in Oberschlesien, das nach dem Sieg √ºber Polen von Deutschland annektiert wurde. Die SS, Adolf Hitlers Terrortruppe, nutzt hierzu eine ehemalige polnische Kaserne, die nach bew√§hrtem Muster umgebaut wird. Ein Jahr sp√§ter, 1941, l√§sst der F√ºhrer der SS, Heinrich Himmler in Auschwitz ein weiteres Lager bauen. Es liegt drei Kilometer entfernt vom bereits bestehenden KZ, das nun Stammlager genannt wird, beim Dorf Brzezinka, das die Deutschen Birkenau nennen. Das Lager wird daher Auschwitz-Birkenau oder Auschwitz 2 genannt. Hier entsteht eine Architektur des Mordes. Die SS organisiert die Vernichtung von Menschen mit industrieller Perfektion: Die Opfer werden per Zug ins Lager deportiert. Ab Fr√ºhjahr 1944 f√ºhren die Bahngleise bis in den Lagerkomplex hinein. So k√∂nnen die Deportierten direkt im Zielort in Empfang genommen werden. SS-√Ñrzte teilen die Ankommenden auf der Rampe in arbeitsf√§hig und nicht-arbeitsf√§hig ein. Alte, Kranke und Kinder gelten grunds√§tzlich als nicht-arbeitsf√§hig. Nach der ‚ÄûAussortierung‚Äú werden die Opfer zum Duschen geschickt. Die Duschk√∂pfe an der Decke sind Attrappen. Entscheidend sind die umgitterten K√§fige, die vom Boden zu einer Luke in der Decke reichen. Es sind Einwurfsch√§chte f√ºr das Gift Zyklon B. Rund 30 Minuten dauert der Todeskampf der Menschen. Danach werden ihre Leichen von der Gaskammer zu den √ñfen gebracht, wo sie verbrannt werden. Alles ist unter einem Dach ‚Äì eine systematische Vernichtung. F√ºr diejenigen, die bei der Ankunft nicht ‚Äûaussortiert‚Äú werden, beginnt die Zwangsarbeit, manche von ihnen werden an die deutsche Kriegsindustrie verkauft. Die Opfer werden nicht nur ermordet und ausgebeutet. Sie werden auch beraubt. Ihr letztes Eigentum wird erst in riesigen Mengen gesammelt und sortiert. Danach wird es in Z√ºgen nach Deutschland geschickt und dort verwertet. Anfang 1945 steht Deutschland kurz vor der Niederlage. Am 27. Januar  befreien Sowjetsoldaten das Lager kampflos. Sie finden grauenvolle Beweise des Verbrechens, die die T√§ter vor ihrer Flucht nicht beseitigen konnten. Und sie sto√üen auf lebende Zeugen: 6000 entkr√§ftete H√§ftlinge, die die SS bei ihrer Flucht zur√ºckgelassen hat. Die Erinnerung an das Grauen von Auschwitz bleibt in den √úberlebenden lebendig, bis heute. 

Dieses Video ist eine Produktion des ZDF.

https://bit.ly/3j6v8MF

üí° Typen der Verst√ºmmelung und Folgen
Die WHO unterscheidet mehrere Typen der weiblichen Genitalverst√ºmmelung: von der Abtrennung des sichtbaren Teils der Klitoris √ºber die Entfernung der Schamlippen bis hin zum Zun√§hen der Vagina. snippet.title: Anne Frank ‚Äì so entstand ihr Tagebuch
snippet.description:
#AnneFrank: Urheberin des wohl ber√ºhmtesten Tagebuchs der Welt. Das Buch, das sie zwischen 1942 und 1944 schreibt, ist bis heute ein Beststeller. Doch Anne Frank hat ihre Geschichte nicht zu Ende erz√§hlen k√∂nnen, sie wurde als J√ºdin von den Nazis verfolgt, gequ√§lt, deportiert und ist im Konzentrationslager Bergen-Belsen leidvoll gestorben. Ihr Tagebuch offenbart uns schonungslos die Gedanken eines √ºber Jahre in Todesangst lebenden jungen M√§dchens ‚Äì ohne dass wir dem Schrecken zumindest teilweise entfliehen k√∂nnen. Denn das Tagebuch erz√§hlt keine Geschichte, die auf Tatsachen beruht, sondern die Geschichte von Anne Frank, die so real und wahr ist, wie die Gedanken eben sind, die man seinem geheimen Tagebuch anvertraut. So wurde das Buch in √ºber 70 Sprachen √ºbersetzt und Generationen von Sch√ºlerinnen und Sch√ºler in aller Welt haben es gelesen. Wer war diese talentierte junge Frau? Wer war Anne Frank?  

In diesem Video gibt Mirko Antworten auf die Fragen. Er folgt der Spur von Anne und ihrer Familie: Wie sie 1933 das nationalsozialistische Deutschland verlassen und in die Niederlande fliehen, wo Anne ihre Jugend verbringt. Er erkl√§rt, wie Anne zum Tagebuch-Schreiben kommt und wie sie den Zweiten Weltkrieg in Amsterdam erlebt. Nat√ºrlich geht es auch darum, wie das Tagebuch gefunden wurde  ‚Äì und warum das Tagebuch so ein wichtiges Zeitdokument ist.  

Wer mehr √ºber die historischen Hintergr√ºnde des Holocaust wissen m√∂chte, findet hier ein Video der Kolleginnen und Kollegen von Terra X:  https://youtu.be/MzuINEWS2sk
